      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know a counselor can talk to me, but it doesn't change the fact that the silence is deafening. it's like there's this massive hole in the world where they used to be. sometimes i sit there for hours just staring at the wall and i realize i'm not even waiting for anything anymore. i'm just... done. it feels so exhausting to keep pretending that life has any substance left when the most important part of it is gone.",
